# --- Expo app (repo root, `app/` — expo-router) ---
# Copy to `.env` at repo root for local dev.
#
# Uses @clerk/expo (see https://clerk.com/docs/quickstarts/expo).
# NEXT_PUBLIC_* on web and EXPO_PUBLIC_* here must use the SAME Clerk publishable key.
# In Clerk Dashboard → Native applications: enable the Native API for Expo.
#
# Push notifications (Expo) — requires a development or production native build (not Expo Go for full token flow on SDK 50+).
# 1. Create/link an Expo project: https://docs.expo.dev/push-notifications/push-notifications-setup/
# 2. Set app.json expo.extra.eas.projectId to your real project UUID from expo.dev / eas.json.
# 3. Run the **API backend** (`OMM_BACKEND` sibling project) so POST /api/mobile/push-token can register tokens.
#
# LOCAL split (recommended): OMM_BACKEND on 3102, apps/web on 3101.
# EXPO_PUBLIC_MOBILE_API_ORIGIN=http://127.0.0.1:3102   # Expo → OMM_BACKEND `/api/mobile/*`
# EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:3102
# EXPO_PUBLIC_WEB_ORIGIN=http://127.0.0.1:3101          # Expo support → apps/web only
# Physical iPhone: LAN IP for 3102 (API) and 3101 (web), or Metro host rewrite in dev.
#
# Legacy split (separate backend on 3102): only if `OMM_BACKEND` implements `/api/mobile/*` — omit EXPO_PUBLIC_WEB_ORIGIN then.
EXPO_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:3101
# Next origin — `/api/mobile/*` is routed here when set:
EXPO_PUBLIC_WEB_ORIGIN=http://127.0.0.1:3101

# --- Web (`apps/web` / Next.js) — copy to `apps/web/.env.local` ---
# NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# Clerk for web (session); same app as Expo.
# Web `/app` → OMM_BACKEND locally:
# NEXT_PUBLIC_BACKEND_URL=http://127.0.0.1:3102
# BACKEND_URL=http://127.0.0.1:3102
# DATABASE_URL + CLERK_* → copy to ../OMM_BACKEND/.env.local (API owns Postgres)
#
# --- API backend (`../OMM_BACKEND`) — see that repo’s `.env.example` ---
# DATABASE_URL — Postgres (backend only now; web no longer connects to DB directly)
# CLERK_SECRET_KEY — verifies Bearer JWTs from Expo + from Next.js server `getToken()`
# CLERK_WEBHOOK_SECRET — Clerk Dashboard webhook → `/api/webhooks/clerk` on the **backend** host
#
# Support & feedback email (Resend). Required for `/api/support/contact` and `/api/support/feedback`.
# Get a key at https://resend.com — use onboarding@resend.dev as RESEND_FROM until your domain is verified.
# RESEND_API_KEY=re_xxxxxxxx
# SUPPORT_INBOX_EMAIL=support@premarket.com.au
# RESEND_FROM_EMAIL=OMM Support <onboarding@resend.dev>
